description:
&lt;p&gt;0.8 WTE is 30 hours per week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic and innovative qualified Clinical Psychologist to join our team providing high quality services to older people within the North East Hants and Farnham areas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that there are other band 7 psychology vacancies across the OPMH division that could be paired with this role to create a full-time (37.5 hours) position if candidates are seeking this. We are happy to discuss available options/flexible working patterns with interested candidates at interview&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This exciting role will involve working autonomously in conducting detailed assessment and formulation, therapeutic intervention and neuropsychological assessments, covering both functional and organic problems for people living in the local community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A key part of this role will be using clinical leadership skills to influence teams in embedding psychosocial approaches within everyday practice. You will also be supporting and supervising unqualified Psychology staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There will be opportunities to lead on quality improvement projects and to contribute to the development of psychology provision across older people’s services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be working collaboratively with members of a well-established multi-disciplinary team, awarded with MSNAP accreditation and Sustainable mental health service commendation. Also the team was accredited with CARE excellence accreditation , where psychology is highly valued. You will be well supported within the psychology team, where CPD and staff support are highly valued and people are encouraged to develop specialist interests in line with evidence-based practice and service needs. For further details please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Phil Anderson:Associate Director of Therapies/Lead Consultant Clinical Psychologist or Rita Gbedebu: Sector Manager NEH&amp;Farnham CMHT OP&lt;/p&gt;
